WEBVTT

01:22.249 --> 01:23.501
Go!

01:24.710 --> 01:27.838
- You said there'd be no shooting!
- I said get the hell out of here!

01:29.799 --> 01:32.343
- Billy!
- Go!

01:43.813 --> 01:46.315
Stop it, Billy. No shooting.
You promised.

01:47.233 --> 01:48.442
Get out of here.

02:30.025 --> 02:34.780
Young lady, I should throw this at you
and sentence you as an adult,

02:36.157 --> 02:40.953
but since this is your first offense,
I'm going to give you a chance

02:41.287 --> 02:42.746
to redeem yourself.

02:43.289 --> 02:45.958
I am sending you to reform school.

02:47.543 --> 02:51.047
You shall be placed in the custody
of the juvenile facilities at Pridemore

02:52.006 --> 02:56.343
for a period of three years,
or until such time as the parole board

02:56.677 --> 02:59.597
determines your release.
Whichever comes first.

03:10.482 --> 03:13.986
- Move over.
- All right, all right.

03:14.486 --> 03:15.738
You scared?

03:16.363 --> 03:19.241
Not anymore,
now that I know the worst is over.

03:19.575 --> 03:20.868
I wish I knew.

03:21.660 --> 03:23.370
I can't stand being locked up.

03:23.787 --> 03:27.124
I'm a runaway. A foster home, third time.

03:27.458 --> 03:28.959
How long are you going in for?

03:29.793 --> 03:31.045
Just until I'm 18.

03:32.463 --> 03:33.964
Then I can live where I want.

03:34.298 --> 03:35.925
You think it's any easier then?

03:37.635 --> 03:39.553
Anything's easier
than living with fosters.

03:39.887 --> 03:41.680
- Ah, forget it. You're a girl.
- Be quiet!

03:43.849 --> 03:46.727
- This ain't no joy ride, girls.
- All right. Yes.

04:34.525 --> 04:35.901
Hey, what's with the tower?

04:36.235 --> 04:37.653
It used to be a water tower.

04:37.987 --> 04:39.238
Now, it's the voice of God.

04:39.571 --> 04:41.073
- Huh?
- You'll see.

04:41.407 --> 04:42.449
Let's go.

04:49.123 --> 04:50.916
Have to be barbed wire and stone walls.

04:51.250 --> 04:52.793
Don't kid yourself.

04:53.127 --> 04:55.379
Worst thing about this place
is the human wall.

04:55.713 --> 04:57.214
Here's the fresh meat.

04:59.550 --> 05:01.593
Nice to see you back, Nicky.

05:02.219 --> 05:04.179
I see I should have kept your file active.

05:04.596 --> 05:07.141
You can wipe your ass with my file, bitch.

05:10.144 --> 05:11.812
All right,
straight ahead to the infirmary,

05:12.146 --> 05:14.523
eyes front, no talking, single file.

05:14.857 --> 05:17.109
Order is the rule here.

05:17.443 --> 05:21.238
Strip down, showers to the left,
physical in 10 minutes.

05:21.572 --> 05:23.115
Get undressed, ladies.

05:41.675 --> 05:45.596
You're going to be inspected
inside and out, so get it clean.

05:47.264 --> 05:48.849
Happy hunting, pig.

05:58.317 --> 05:59.735
Shake out your hair.

06:02.863 --> 06:04.114
Turn around.

06:07.368 --> 06:08.911
Bend over.

06:09.828 --> 06:11.413
Spread 'em wide.

06:13.999 --> 06:15.959
Clothes in the hamper.
Be sure your name tag's on.

06:16.293 --> 06:19.588
Personals in the basket.
Move it on.

06:21.006 --> 06:23.050
Ragdoll, too, honey.
This ain't no kindergarten.

06:23.425 --> 06:25.010
No, please.
It's all I have.

06:25.386 --> 06:27.346
Come on, hand it over.
You're a big girl, now.

06:27.679 --> 06:29.556
Please, it was Joey's. I promised.

06:30.015 --> 06:32.643
Please. No, please, please.

06:34.478 --> 06:36.021
All right, all right.
It gets past me,

06:36.355 --> 06:39.691
but I'm not the final word here.
Clothes in the hamper.

06:40.025 --> 06:42.528
Be sure your name tags are on.
Personals in the basket.

06:42.861 --> 06:44.988
- Move it on.
- State your size.

06:45.322 --> 06:46.532
Small, medium, or large?

06:46.865 --> 06:48.075
Small.

06:48.659 --> 06:51.078
- Small.
- Don't worry about style.

06:51.495 --> 06:53.580
- Same this year as the last.
- Small.

06:55.958 --> 06:57.626
Medium.

07:05.134 --> 07:06.760
Come on in.
St down, Jennifer.

07:11.682 --> 07:13.475
- Friends call you Jenny?
- Yes, ma'am.

07:14.184 --> 07:15.894
- May I?
- I guess so.

07:16.770 --> 07:20.691
Good, I'd like that.
I'm Dr. Norton, psychologist.

07:21.066 --> 07:23.652
I've been assigned here to work
with the girls on the inside.

07:24.153 --> 07:26.321
Listen to your problems, help you cope.

07:27.156 --> 07:29.074
I know it's difficult being in here.

07:29.575 --> 07:32.327
The judge said I might get parole.
When would that be?

07:32.744 --> 07:36.331
Well, you're here for three years,
so you won't be eligible

07:36.665 --> 07:38.876
for at least 14 months
and a lot of that depends

07:39.209 --> 07:40.836
on your behavior and your attitude.

07:41.378 --> 07:42.963
- Yes, ma'am.
- Smoke?

07:43.464 --> 07:44.506
Yes.

07:45.048 --> 07:48.343
I see in your file
that your father's your legal guardian.

07:49.386 --> 07:51.054
How's he feel about you being here?

07:51.680 --> 07:52.639
He doesn't care.

07:52.973 --> 07:54.349
We don't like each other much.

07:54.766 --> 07:55.642
Why not?

07:55.976 --> 07:57.728
When my mom died,
he said I could come live with him

07:58.061 --> 07:59.646
so I wouldn't have to live
in a foster home.

08:00.063 --> 08:01.023
You didn't get along?

08:01.356 --> 08:04.026
Well, he liked me a lot at first,
when I was little.

08:04.359 --> 08:05.819
What happened?

08:06.153 --> 08:08.864
As I got older, I made him stop.

08:09.198 --> 08:10.824
Stop?

08:11.158 --> 08:12.993
Liking me so much.

08:13.327 --> 08:15.579
- You mean he molested you?
- Yes, ma'am.

08:15.913 --> 08:18.248
- Didn't you ever tell anybody?
- I was too scared.

08:18.582 --> 08:21.335
I just made sure he stayed away
when I got older.

08:23.337 --> 08:24.963
I learned to handle myself okay.

08:27.049 --> 08:28.467
Not well enough.

08:28.800 --> 08:30.093
You're here.

08:31.303 --> 08:33.722
I think you're gonna do just fine, Jenny.

08:34.056 --> 08:36.266
You're new here and so am I.

08:36.600 --> 08:38.268
I hope you and the other girls
will come to me,

08:38.602 --> 08:40.020
tell me what it's like in here.

08:40.354 --> 08:44.358
I'll listen and I'll work with you
to make it as easy as I can.

08:44.691 --> 08:47.027
- Got a deal?
- It's a deal.

08:54.743 --> 08:57.371
Hey, told that Norton dame about us.

08:57.704 --> 08:59.331
She said we were okay.

08:59.665 --> 09:01.375
If we bunk together,
will you be my friend?

09:01.708 --> 09:03.794
I already am.

09:13.178 --> 09:15.764
Vote's in.
Here's the new shipment.

09:19.726 --> 09:21.853
I thought I smelled fish.

09:24.189 --> 09:26.650
Welcome to our country club, ladies.

09:26.984 --> 09:29.194
This is the last stop on your tour.

09:31.446 --> 09:33.365
Home, you might call it.

09:35.242 --> 09:41.164
Nicky, I see that flip tongue of yours
didn't get you so far on the outside.

09:41.498 --> 09:44.126
Outsmarted yourself again, didn't you?

09:45.877 --> 09:47.421
Who's your new friend?

09:47.754 --> 09:49.715
This here's Kelly.
She's with me.

09:50.048 --> 09:51.341
She's okay.

09:51.675 --> 09:53.510
I'm sure she is.

09:53.844 --> 09:56.388
Too bad the two of you
won't be bunking together.

09:56.722 --> 10:00.309
Take these three to number 17.
These three bunk here.

10:00.642 --> 10:02.561
Dr. Norton said we could bunk together.

10:02.894 --> 10:04.354
She said we was okay.

10:04.688 --> 10:06.773
Norton don't make the rules.

10:07.107 --> 10:10.068
I do.
You should know that by now, dear.

10:10.402 --> 10:12.112
She ain't never been in here before.

10:12.446 --> 10:14.906
She needs me to help her make it.

10:15.240 --> 10:17.951
Everyone's a first-timer once.

10:18.285 --> 10:19.244
Get her out of here.

10:19.578 --> 10:21.163
- Okay, come on girls. Come on.
- Nicky, I don't want to go.

10:21.496 --> 10:24.249
- I don't want to go.
- You know the routine, Nicky.

10:29.338 --> 10:33.592
Jennifer Williams, Lisa Stewart,
and of course, Nicky.

10:35.177 --> 10:38.597
You may be numbers to all the rest,
but not to me.

10:39.139 --> 10:41.433
You do things right, and we'll get along.

10:42.559 --> 10:44.394
I run a good, tight dorm.

10:44.936 --> 10:46.229
Right, Nicky?

10:46.563 --> 10:48.732
The only thing tight about you
are your pants.

10:51.318 --> 10:53.779
I'll remember that remark.

10:54.154 --> 10:55.781
I'm the head matron here.

10:56.156 --> 10:58.950
You answer to me on every count.

10:59.284 --> 11:03.413
My name's Edna, but some of the girls
call me Eddie

11:04.373 --> 11:06.166
after they get to know me better.

11:07.084 --> 11:08.293
I like that.

11:08.877 --> 11:11.129
You might like it, too, after a while.

11:17.386 --> 11:20.222
I expect full cooperation.

11:22.974 --> 11:24.351
- That doll, I got to take it.
- No.

11:24.685 --> 11:26.311
- We got rules.
- Can't she keep it?

11:26.645 --> 11:28.814
- It's real important to her.
- Speaking out of turn?

11:29.147 --> 11:31.233
Did you hear
what I said about cooperation?

11:31.566 --> 11:33.151
The nurses said she could keep it.

11:33.485 --> 11:34.986
Oh, I'm impressed.

11:43.578 --> 11:45.163
It'll be safe with me.

11:46.748 --> 11:51.128
You want to see it from time to time,
you just ask me nicely.

11:55.215 --> 11:57.134
Now, let's go to the dorm.

11:59.469 --> 12:01.304
- Anyway, I called her.
- Give it back.

12:32.794 --> 12:38.091
Come out, sweethearts. Come out.

12:43.680 --> 12:45.724
There are three empties down back.

12:46.057 --> 12:51.897
You take 17, and you 19,
and you get the upper, number 20.

12:52.481 --> 12:54.191
Dinner in an hour.

13:14.503 --> 13:16.588
- I can fix it for you.
- Come on, over here.

13:16.922 --> 13:18.590
All right, you mug.

13:18.924 --> 13:22.135
Just because you've been here longer,
don't mean you're getting out sooner.

13:39.986 --> 13:43.240
Lisa, Edna told you to take 17.

13:43.573 --> 13:46.493
- Seventeen's taken, fish bait.
- Yes.

13:46.827 --> 13:48.745
Well, Edna just told her to take it.

13:49.079 --> 13:50.121
Whoa.

13:50.455 --> 13:53.124
- Listen, sister.
- Thanks, but I'm not your sister.

13:53.834 --> 13:55.335
It's okay, Jenny.
I don't mind.

13:55.669 --> 13:56.920
You should mind.

13:57.254 --> 13:58.755
You heard what Edna said about the rules.

13:59.089 --> 14:00.799
- The rules?
- How about if I just move your stuff

14:01.132 --> 14:02.634
- to the upper?
- Later, baby cake.

14:02.968 --> 14:05.720
How about if I move your ass
across the floor?

14:06.054 --> 14:08.974
Bullseye booked
for child molesting, film at 11.

14:10.433 --> 14:12.644
- Let it rest, Jenny.
- "Let it rest, Jenny."

14:13.019 --> 14:14.688
Your friend has the right idea.

14:15.021 --> 14:17.774
My friend may be afraid of you,
but I'm not.

14:18.149 --> 14:21.152
- Whoa.
- I said lay off it, sister.

15:08.617 --> 15:09.618
- Come on.
- Give it to her.

15:09.951 --> 15:11.661
- Break it up.
- Come on, come on, come on.

15:11.995 --> 15:13.997
I see you're going to have
a hard time adjusting.

15:14.331 --> 15:15.540
I was adjusting.

15:15.874 --> 15:19.878
Don't you contradict me,
you insolent bitch.

15:20.211 --> 15:22.422
Stirring the shit already, huh?

15:23.548 --> 15:24.925
What happened, Charlie?

15:25.383 --> 15:27.552
She was throwing my personals around.

15:27.844 --> 15:28.970
Yes, that's right.

15:29.304 --> 15:31.389
Girl ain't got much on the inside.

15:31.723 --> 15:33.892
What little she does have is personal.

15:35.226 --> 15:39.272
Messing with another girl's personals
is against the rules.

15:39.648 --> 15:41.691
You just lost one privilege.

15:42.025 --> 15:45.278
- But she --
- Speaking out of turn is another rule.

15:45.737 --> 15:47.572
Want to lose two privileges?

15:49.866 --> 15:56.122
The name of the game, ladies,
is control. Complete control.

15:57.791 --> 16:01.044
- Everyone into your bunks until dinner.
- Oh, no.

16:01.378 --> 16:03.296
Thanks. A lot of thanks.

16:03.630 --> 16:05.340
You did this, you know?

16:54.472 --> 16:55.682
Silence.

16:59.894 --> 17:01.312
Fishlips and rice.

17:01.646 --> 17:02.981
It must be Wednesday.

17:08.778 --> 17:11.114
I guess some people order
from a different menu.

17:17.912 --> 17:21.041
Hey, Charlie, looks like
the rookie's giving you the eye.

17:25.587 --> 17:28.423
Don't cost nothing to look.

17:28.757 --> 17:31.092
I don't know about that.

17:31.760 --> 17:33.595
Give me the box lunch.

17:38.016 --> 17:39.809
Don't bust your straps yet, Knox.

17:40.143 --> 17:41.936
You'll get yours in the end.

17:45.231 --> 17:47.817
- No.
- You lost one privilege.

17:48.151 --> 17:49.903
I decided it's dinner.

17:50.236 --> 17:52.113
Let's go, get up.

18:21.935 --> 18:23.520
I like the way you took on Charlie today.

18:23.853 --> 18:25.980
Ain't many fish that would fuck with Char.

18:26.314 --> 18:27.524
I didn't know who I was messing with.

18:27.857 --> 18:30.110
It seems like Charlie and Edna
have an understanding.

18:30.443 --> 18:32.654
Yeah, Charlie is under
and Edna is standing.

18:34.781 --> 18:35.990
My name is Paula.

18:36.324 --> 18:37.826
- Hi.
- Nice to meet you.

18:38.159 --> 18:39.744
- This is Lisa.
- Hi, Lisa.

18:40.078 --> 18:41.329
Hi.

18:42.413 --> 18:46.918
Here, stay cool. You're okay.

18:48.378 --> 18:50.505
That's Claudia, poor sucker.

18:50.922 --> 18:53.716
- What happened to her?
- She blocked out last month.

18:54.134 --> 18:56.052
- Blocked out?
- Yes, but they caught her

18:56.386 --> 18:58.179
and flipped her back in,
and now she get to do her time

18:58.513 --> 19:01.057
- all over again.
- You asshole.

19:08.606 --> 19:14.154
You know, we got off to a bad start,
but now that Edna evened the score,

19:14.487 --> 19:16.030
maybe we can start fresh.

19:16.364 --> 19:18.074
My name is Charlie.

19:18.408 --> 19:20.785
- I know who you are.
- These here are my girls.

19:21.119 --> 19:24.164
You call them girls? Hey.

19:25.540 --> 19:26.958
Still going to play it cool, huh?

19:27.292 --> 19:29.252
I'm not going to play at all.

19:29.586 --> 19:34.174
Listen, snob, you better learn real fast
about life behind the iron here,

19:34.507 --> 19:37.010
because it's real important
who you move with.

19:40.889 --> 19:45.518
Things would be real easy for you
if you and your friend would decide

19:45.852 --> 19:47.937
to fall in with me and my girls.

19:48.271 --> 19:52.650
The proud crowd, huh? Thanks.
I pick my own friends.

19:54.027 --> 20:00.909
Might I remind you that your friend
is the local scum sucker around here.

20:01.284 --> 20:03.578
And you ain't as Dutch blood,
you motherfucking dyke.

20:03.912 --> 20:06.247
Take that back
if you ever want to talk again.

20:06.581 --> 20:10.335
You take that back if you ever want
to wag that tongue of yours again.

20:10.668 --> 20:12.378
Stop it.
Let her alone.

20:12.712 --> 20:16.007
- Do it.
- Open up. Open up.

20:16.341 --> 20:18.509
- Stop.
- Open up.

20:20.845 --> 20:22.889
Hey, ditch it, you guys.
Big pig's coming.

20:23.223 --> 20:24.474
It's lights out.

20:26.935 --> 20:30.146
- This ain't settled yet, white bread.
- Bet your ass it ain't.

20:44.118 --> 20:47.830
Count down. All right?

20:48.414 --> 20:50.291
Let's play the name game.

20:50.625 --> 20:51.876
- Charmin, Karen.

20:52.210 --> 20:53.920
- Eldrige, Andrea.
- Stewart, Lisa.

20:54.254 --> 20:55.505
- Locke, Becky.
- Chambliss, Charlie.

20:55.838 --> 20:56.923
Williams, Jennifer.

20:57.257 --> 20:58.425
- Adam, Nicky.
- Belgrave, Nina.

20:58.758 --> 21:00.301
- Johnson, Paula.
- Lawson, Claudia.

21:00.635 --> 21:02.553
- Eileen, Terry.
- Gabriel, Terry.

21:06.599 --> 21:08.268
Lights out.

21:08.726 --> 21:10.228
No talking.

21:17.568 --> 21:21.489
Remember,
keep your fingers above the sheets.

21:21.823 --> 21:24.450
We only change them once a week.

21:32.208 --> 21:36.212
Mother of salvation, shrine of holiness
and mercy,

21:36.546 --> 21:40.466
I long to come before you in my misery,
sick with corruption,

21:40.883 --> 21:45.471
in pain from the wounds of crimes,
putrid with the sores of sin.

21:45.972 --> 21:48.850
I am so filthy and disgusting
that I am afraid

21:49.183 --> 21:50.768
you will turn your back on me.

21:51.436 --> 21:57.775
Hear me, good lady, and I bless the soul
of the sinner who is contrite. Amen.

22:00.737 --> 22:02.280
Hey, watch it.

22:08.995 --> 22:11.205
Hey, morning will be here quicker
than you think.

22:11.539 --> 22:14.000
I can never sleep in a strange bed.

22:14.334 --> 22:16.753
Don't think of it as strange.

22:17.086 --> 22:18.880
I decided I'm going to think of this
as summer camp

22:19.213 --> 22:21.173
and we'll be going home soon.
- Shhh.

22:21.507 --> 22:23.384
Hey, knock it off down there, you two.

22:23.718 --> 22:25.803
You want Miss Dread back up here again?

24:33.055 --> 24:35.766
- What is it?
- Lisa?

24:36.100 --> 24:37.810
Oh, my god, it's Lisa.

24:38.144 --> 24:39.896
Don't get yourself into it, god damn it.

24:40.229 --> 24:42.064
- She's so weak.
- You can't.

24:42.398 --> 24:43.483
Let me go.

24:44.442 --> 24:47.487
- Halt right there, young lady.
- What are they doing to her?

24:58.748 --> 25:02.293
You little brat,
you're as heavy as lead. Come on.

25:06.380 --> 25:10.009
Seems like you new girls are having
some trouble getting adjusted.

25:10.551 --> 25:14.931
I know I have a beautiful voice,
but I don't make these rules

25:15.264 --> 25:17.058
to hear myself talk.

25:17.433 --> 25:24.232
So far today, it's been two girls
and two infractions, and that's too much.

25:25.191 --> 25:27.610
You'll all be written up
and confined tomorrow

25:27.944 --> 25:30.488
if there's any more trouble
from this group.

25:31.405 --> 25:32.698
Take care of your friend.

25:33.032 --> 25:35.910
She just had a little accident.

25:36.244 --> 25:38.788
Oh, come on, man.

26:13.698 --> 26:16.117
- Hi.
- Hi.

26:16.450 --> 26:17.994
Charlie's got your number.

26:18.327 --> 26:20.997
I wouldn't leave myself out
in the open too much if I were you.

26:21.330 --> 26:25.501
Thanks,
and thanks for the bread last night.

26:25.835 --> 26:27.628
- It helped.
- My pleasure.

26:33.926 --> 26:35.219
What are those marks?

26:41.475 --> 26:43.311
I don't see no marks.

26:43.644 --> 26:45.229
Those marks on those girls.

26:45.563 --> 26:49.692
I said, I don't see no marks,
and neither do you.

26:59.410 --> 27:00.870
Your friend Lisa still out?

27:01.203 --> 27:01.996
Yeah.

27:02.330 --> 27:04.332
She's in the infirmary,
threw up all night.

27:17.637 --> 27:22.850
You butthole sisters
better wash your things real good,

27:23.184 --> 27:27.605
because we don't want
none of your crotch rot in our dorm.

27:37.365 --> 27:39.116
- Hey.
- Shine it on.

27:40.743 --> 27:44.497
I want to see that honkey bitch get hers
before I bop out of this place.

27:45.289 --> 27:48.042
It's coming.
Baby, it's coming.

27:53.506 --> 27:56.634
I see from your report
you've listed all of Lisa's infractions,

27:56.967 --> 28:00.721
but you've made no attempt to indicate
what might've provoked her behavior.

28:01.055 --> 28:03.265
Troublemaker's a troublemaker.

28:03.599 --> 28:06.811
All these girls are here
because they broke the rules.

28:07.520 --> 28:10.022
It's not my job to find out why.

28:10.731 --> 28:13.275
I'm here to see they don't break anymore.

28:13.609 --> 28:14.944
I see.

28:17.905 --> 28:20.616
Well,
perhaps I'd better speak to Lisa alone.

28:21.242 --> 28:22.660
